borrow(uint256,uint256).details: Only te owner of a vault can borrow from it. `borrow()` will update the outstanding vault debt to the current time before attempting the withdrawal. and will fail if it would bring the vault below the liquidation treshold.

params._amount: the amount of borrowed StableX tokens in WEI.*
params._vaultId: the ID of the vault from which to borrow.

deposit(address,uint256).details: A new vault is created if no vault exists for the `msg.sender` with the specified collateral type. this function used `transferFrom()` and requires pre-approval via `approve()` on the ERC20.

params._amount: the amount of tokens to be deposited in WEI.*
params._collateralType: the address of the collateral type to be deposited
the address of the new collateral type to be initialized*

liquidate(uint256).details: `liquidate()` will update the outstanding vault debt to the current time and pay a `liquidationBonus` to the liquidator. `liquidate()` can be called by anyone.

params._vaultId: the ID of the vault to be liquidated.*

refreshCollateral(address).details: this updates the debt for all vaults with the specified collateral type.

params._collateralType: the address of the collateral type to be refreshed.*

repay(uint256,uint256).details: `repay()` will update the outstanding vault debt to the current time.

params._amount: the amount of StableX tokens in WEI to be repaid.*
params._vaultId: the ID of the vault for which to repay the outstanding debt balance.

repayAll(uint256).details: `repayAll()` will update the outstanding vault debt to the current time.

params._vaultId: the ID of the vault for which to repay the debt.*

withdraw(uint256,uint256).details: Only te owner of a vault can withdraw collateral from it. `withdraw()` will fail if it would bring the vault below the liquidation treshold.

params._amount: the amount of ERC20 tokens to be withdrawn in WEI.*
params._vaultId: the ID of the vault from which to withdraw the collateral.

withdrawAll(uint256).details: Only te owner of a vault can withdraw collateral from it. `withdrawAll()` will fail if the vault has any outstanding debt attached to it.

params._vaultId: the ID of the vault from which to withdraw the collateral.*

borrow(uint256,uint256).notice: Borrow new StableX (Eg: PAR) tokens from a vault.

deposit(address,uint256).notice: Deposit an ERC20 token into the vault of the msg.sender as collateral

initializeRates(address).notice: Initialize the cumulative rates to 1 for a new collateral type.

liquidate(uint256).notice: Liquidate a vault that is below the liquidation treshold by repaying it's outstanding debt.

refresh().notice: Refresh the cumulative rates and debts of all vaults and all collateral types.*

refreshCollateral(address).notice: Refresh the cumulative rate of a collateraltype.

repay(uint256,uint256).notice: Repay an outstanding StableX balance to a vault.

repayAll(uint256).notice: Convenience function to repay all debt of a vault

withdraw(uint256,uint256).notice: Withdraws ERC20 tokens from a vault.

withdrawAll(uint256).notice: Convenience function to withdraw all collateral of a vault
